The paper discusses the use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) in machine learning, specifically in the irregular spatial domain. This suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper utilizes graph signal processing techniques, which may fall under the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on the MNIST digit classification problem, which may also place it under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
